---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Open Positions">
	<section class="mb-16 px-1 pt-4">
		<h1 class="mb-12 text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight break-words text-black md:text-6xl">
			Open Positions at reAIM
		</h1>

		<div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-12 lg:flex-row">
			<div class="min-w-0 flex-1 space-y-8 text-xl leading-relaxed text-gray-800">
				<p>Thank you for your interest in joining the reAIM lab!</p>

				<div
					class="border-reaim-blue w-full max-w-4xl rounded-r-xl border-l-4 bg-gray-50 p-6 md:p-8"
				>
					<div class="space-y-1">
						<p class="text-xl font-bold break-words text-black">
							Please read the following page in its entirety before reaching out to us.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p>
					Our lab is always looking for students with a strong computational background, not afraid
					to dive deep into multiple subfields of learning, and an interest in impactful AI for
					health, while contributing to methodological and human-centered advances in AI.
				</p>
				<p>
					Dr. Joshi is an Assistant Professor at the <a
						href="https://www.dbmi.columbia.edu/faculty/"
						class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline"
						>Department of Biomedical Informatics (DBMI)</a
					>, an affiliate of the <a
						href="https://www.cs.columbia.edu/people/affiliates/"
						class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">Department of Computer Science</a
					>, and a member of the <a
						href="https://datascience.columbia.edu/people/shalmali-joshi/"
						class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">Data Science Institute (DSI)</a
					>. Consequently, there are several avenues for students and researchers to join our lab:
				</p>

				<h3 class="mt-10 border-t border-gray-100 pt-6 text-3xl font-bold break-words text-black">
					Doctoral Students
				</h3>

				<p>Doctoral students can join reAIM via the following programs:</p>
				<ul class="ml-6 list-outside list-disc space-y-2 pl-1">
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://www.dbmi.columbia.edu/phd-in-biomedical-informatics/"
							class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">Biomedical Informatics</a
						> through <a
							href="https://www.vagelos.columbia.edu/education/academic-programs/vagelos-institutes-biomedical-research-education/phd-programs"
							class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline"
							>Vagelos Instituteâ€™s Biomedical Research Education (VIBRE)</a
						> at the Columbia University Irving Medical Center.
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://www.cs.columbia.edu/education/phd/"
							class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">Computer Science</a
						> at the <a
							href="https://www.gradengineering.columbia.edu/academics/graduate/doctoral"
							class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline"
							>Fu Foundation School of Engineering and Applied Science</a
						>.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<p>
					Given the individual nature of the degree and our lab's focus on machine learning to a
					wide range of topics relevant to healthcare, thesis work will be driven by the student's
					research regardless of which program they join. The key difference is in core coursework
					and milestones: <a
						href="https://www.dbmi.columbia.edu/courses/"
						class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">DBMI students</a
					> will take classes on symbolic methods, clinical informatics, and healthcare delivery, while
					<a
						href="https://www.cs.columbia.edu/education/phd/requirements/"
						class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">Computer Science</a
					> students will take courses in algorithms and systems. Students in both departments will take
					electives according to their research interests. We will allocate desk space and resources at
					our offices located at the <a
						href="https://universitylife.columbia.edu/content/maps-locations"
						class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">medical center (CUIMC) campus</a
					> regardless of which department the student joins.
				</p>

				<p class="text-reaim-dark font-bold">
					Please note your interest in working with Dr. Shalmali Joshi in your application.
				</p>

				<p>
					If you are already admitted to the PhD program at DBMI at Columbia, you are welcome to
					reach out to Dr. Joshi to do a rotation with reAIM lab!
				</p>

				<h3 class="mt-10 border-t border-gray-100 pt-6 text-3xl font-bold break-words text-black">
					Postdoctoral Researchers
				</h3>

				<ul class="ml-6 list-outside list-disc space-y-3 pl-1">
					<li>
						Postdoctoral openings via the Department of Biomedical Informatics will be posted on our
						website and the <a
							href="https://www.dbmi.columbia.edu/dbmi-careers/"
							class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">DBMI Careers</a
						> page.
					</li>
					<li>
						Postdoctoral researchers can also join DBMI via the Department's <a
							href="https://www.dbmi.columbia.edu/postdoctoral-fellowship-degree/"
							class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline"
							>National Library of Medicine (NLM) Training Grant</a
						> if they are U.S. Citizens or Permanent Residents. The NLM fellowship gives two years of
						support.
					</li>
					<li>
						The <a
							href="https://datascience.columbia.edu/research/postdoctoral-researchers/"
							class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">Data Science Institute</a
						> also hosts postdoctoral fellows. The program does not have citizenship requirements and
						supports researchers for two years via year-long renewable appointments.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="mt-10 border-t border-gray-100 pt-6 text-3xl font-bold break-words text-black">
					Master's and Undergraduate Students
				</h3>

				<p>
					If you are a <strong>current</strong> master's or undergraduate student at Columbia University
					interested in rotating in our lab, please reach out to Dr. Joshi with the following:
				</p>
				<ul class="ml-6 list-outside list-disc space-y-2 pl-1">
					<li>Your program, major, expected year of graduation.</li>
					<li>Your research interests and how they align with reAIM.</li>
					<li>Your goals for the rotation.</li>
					<li>The amount of time you can commit to research this semester.</li>
					<li>Contact information for references.</li>
					<li>
						Grades at any courses relevant to Machine Learning (e.g. Linear Algebra, Probability and
						Statistics, Optimization, etc.).
					</li>
					<li>Attach your unofficial Columbia and undergraduate (if applicable) transcripts.</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="mt-10 border-t border-gray-100 pt-6 text-3xl font-bold break-words text-black">
					Visiting Researchers and Outside Collaborators
				</h3>

				<p>
					Please contact Dr. Joshi if you are an external researcher interested in visiting or
					collaborating with our lab.
				</p>

				<div class="mt-12 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6 md:p-8">
					<h3 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-black">For All Applicants:</h3>
					<p class="break-words">
						The best way to get in contact with the lab is by emailing Professor Joshi at <code
							class="inline-block max-w-full rounded border border-gray-300 bg-white px-2 py-1 text-lg break-all"
							>shalmali[dot]joshi[at]columbia.edu</code
						>.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-6">
						<span class="text-reaim-dark font-bold"
							>Please include <code>[reAIM / AHAR]</code> to the title of your email.*</span
						>
					</p>
					<p class="mt-6 text-base text-gray-500 italic">
						* AHAR: All Hail <a
							href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Avatar:_The_Last_Airbender_characters#Supporting_characters_and_organizations/"
							class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">Avatar Roku</a
						>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="flex w-full shrink-0 flex-col gap-8 lg:w-80">
				<div class="w-full">
					<img
						src="/images/reaim_group_photo_2025.jpg"
						alt="2025 Group Photo"
						class="h-auto w-full rounded-xl bg-gray-100 shadow-md"
					/>
					<p class="mt-2 text-center text-sm font-bold text-gray-700">
						reAIM Lab Dinner, Fall 2025
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="w-full">
					<img
						src="/images/reaim_group_photo_2024.jpg"
						alt="2024 Group Photo"
						class="h-auto w-full rounded-xl bg-gray-100 shadow-md"
					/>
					<p class="mt-2 text-center text-sm font-bold text-gray-700">
						reAIM @ <a
							href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_Botanical_Garden"
							class="text-reaim-blue font-bold hover:underline">NYBG</a
						>, Spring 2024
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
